3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"OKX calculates funding rates every 8 hours at 04:00, 12:00, and 20:00 UTC using a time-weighted average of the premium index over the previous 8-hour period. The funding fee is exchanged directly between long and short position holders, with OKX taking no cut from the funding mechanism. Portfolio margin mode allows traders to offset funding payments across correlated positions, reducing net funding costs and enabling more complex arbitrage structures."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","BTC","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BTC/USDT represents OKX's highest volume perpetual contract with consistently predictable funding patterns during trending markets. The pair's deep liquidity ensures minimal slippage when establishing large arbitrage positions, while the 8-hour funding frequency provides multiple daily opportunities to capture rate differentials against other exchanges."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"OKX BTC/USDT funding rates typically range from -0.01% to 0.375% per 8-hour period, with extreme rates during major market moves reaching 0.75%. Bull markets consistently produce positive funding rates as long positions dominate, often sustaining 0.1-0.3% rates for weeks. Bear market periods show more volatile funding with frequent negative rates as shorts accumulate. Weekend trading often exhibits lower funding volatility due to reduced institutional activity, creating opportunities for rate arbitrage against exchanges with different user bases."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"OKX's 8-hour funding cycle creates systematic arbitrage opportunities against Binance's 8-hour and Bybit's variable funding schedules. Portfolio margin enables delta-neutral strategies where traders can short BTC/USDT perpetuals on OKX while holding equivalent long positions on exchanges offering lower funding rates. The exchange's API infrastructure supports automated funding rate monitoring and position management across multiple venues. Cross-margin efficiency often makes OKX competitive even when funding rates are slightly higher, as reduced margin requirements improve capital efficiency."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"OKX's portfolio margin system, while capital-efficient, can amplify liquidation risk during volatile periods as correlations between positions change rapidly. Funding rate arbitrage on BTC/USDT requires monitoring basis risk between perpetual and spot prices, especially during funding payment windows. The exchange's complex product lineup can lead to unintended position interactions in portfolio margin mode. Regulatory uncertainty around OKX's global operations poses potential access risks for funding rate strategies requiring consistent market access across multiple time zones."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What time does funding occur for BTC/USDT on OKX?","answer":"Funding payments occur every 8 hours at 04:00, 12:00, and 20:00 UTC. Positions held at these exact times will pay or receive funding based on the calculated rate for that period."},{"question":"How does OKX's portfolio margin affect BTC funding strategies?","answer":"Portfolio margin allows you to offset BTC perpetual positions against correlated assets, reducing overall margin requirements. This enables larger position sizes for funding arbitrage, but increases liquidation risk if correlations break down during volatile markets."},{"question":"Can I avoid funding fees on OKX BTC/USDT perpetuals?","answer":"You can avoid funding fees by closing positions before funding times, but this eliminates arbitrage opportunities. Alternatively, maintaining balanced long and short exposure across different timeframes can minimize net funding impact while preserving market exposure."},{"question":"What's the maximum funding rate for BTC/USDT on OKX?","answer":"OKX caps funding rates at ±0.75% per 8-hour period for BTC/USDT. During extreme market conditions, rates may hit these caps, creating significant arbitrage opportunities against exchanges with different rate limits or calculation methods."}]}]
